@startuml sq_mcp01_connect_mcp_server
' ============================================================
' Title:     MCP-01 — CONNECT MCP Server
' Boundary:  nasim code agent
' Purpose:   Connect to external MCP server via stdio/SSE
' Milestone: v1.0
' Version:   1.0.0
' Source:    docs/UC/README.md
' Review:    docs/audit/audit.2026.06.20.sq-sm-chain.car.md
' ============================================================

title nasim — MCP-01 CONNECT MCP Server

' Participants with box colors per C4 layer

note over participants
  Scope:          Connection establishment to external MCP server
  Preconditions:  MCP server endpoint configured in agent settings
  Excludes:       Tool discovery and adaptation (see MCP-02, MCP-03)
  Contexts:       Agent initialization, server reconnection
  Rollback:       Close socket on failure, retry with backoff
  Design:         Connection pooling and heartbeat monitoring
end note

== MCP-01 CONNECT MCP Server ==

AgentOrchestrator -> MCPClientRuntime: connect(server_config)
MCPClientRuntime -> External MCP Server: establish stdio/SSE connection
External MCP Server --> MCPClientRuntime: connection established
MCPClientRuntime -> External MCP Server: send initialize handshake
External MCP Server --> MCPClientRuntime: handshake response (capabilities)
MCPClientRuntime -> MCPClientRuntime: store connection state
MCPClientRuntime --> AgentOrchestrator: connection ready

note over participants
  Flow:    Establish connection -> handshake -> ready
  State:   disconnected -> connecting -> connected -> ready
  Failure: Connection refused/timeout -> retry with exponential backoff
  Success: Agent receives ready connection handle
end note

@enduml